-- BOJ's Shirakawa Says Export Demand Will Keep Japan's Economy Expanding
-- Mayumi Otsuma
-- 2010-07-08T00:33:00Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-08/boj-s-shirakawa-says-export-demand-will-keep-japan-s-economy-expanding.html

          
          
             Bank of Japan Governor Masaaki
Shirakawa said the world’s second-largest economy will keep
expanding, driven by demand from abroad.  
 The pace of growth in exports and production will moderate
and domestic demand is likely to pick up, Shirakawa said at a
quarterly meeting of the central bank’s branch managers in Tokyo
today.  
